<p>There have been many threads on this already (<a href="http://stackoverflow.com/questions/28053488/force-matplotlibrc-to-use-arial-paht-of-font">Force matplotlibrc to use Arial (paht of font)</a>, <a href="http://stackoverflow.com/questions/16574898/how-to-load-ttf-file-in-matplotlib-using-mpl-rcparams">How to load .ttf file in matplotlib using mpl.rcParams?</a>). None seems to help in my case. I have number of fonts installed on my system and registered in matplotlib. Everything seems to work when I am in the shell:</p>  <pre><code>&gt;&gt;&gt; import matplotlib as mpl &gt;&gt;&gt; from matplotlib import font_manager &gt;&gt;&gt; path = '/usr/share/fonts/truetype/msttcorefonts/Times_New_Roman.ttf' &gt;&gt;&gt; props = font_manager.FontProperties(fname=path) &gt;&gt;&gt; print props family=Times New Roman ... file=/usr/.../Times_New_Roman.ttf ... &gt;&gt;&gt; mpl.rcParams['font.family'] = props.get_name() &gt;&gt;&gt; mpl.rcParams RcParams({...,u'font.family': [u'Times New Roman'], ... }) </code></pre>  <p>However, when I try to do the same in a script and run it (and I have tried a dozen times), I get:</p>  <pre><code>/usr/local/lib/python2.7/dist-packages/matplotlib/font_manager.py:1282: UserWarning: findfont: Font family [u'Times New Roman'] not found. </code></pre>  <p>Why?</p>